				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Twenty Four<a name="71886"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 6 05 8:08 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>This idea has been in my head for some time now, and i'd like to share it with you all to see what you think.
<br />

<br />
The idea is simple: Creating a guild / raid force of 24 players; how far through EQ could you get?
<br />

<br />
The first obstable is classes. You've only got 24 spaces to fill, and with 16 classes there's not much room left! I've spent hours playing around with what I think would be the best 4-group combination to take you from your first raids, right up to PoP encounters and beyond. However with little to no raid experience, I find this difficult to do as I only have what I can find on sites etc to rely on. 
<br />

<br />
Now some of you may already be thinking that this would be impossible to implement. To get the same 24 people to consistently be online 4-5 days a week, every week would be practically impossible. There's also 100 more reasons why this would be hard to do; but I'm asking you to detact yourself from reality for a moment and go with me on this. Humour me if you will.
<br />

<br />
Here's the main question:
<br />

<br />
 You've got 24 spaces, and 4 groups to fill. Each player will be lvl 65+, with the first few basic aa's gained (say the top 30 for each class). The aim is to get as far through EQ raid content as possible, using the same 24 people. 
<br />
Here's what i've come up with, albeit with limited knowledge of all classes:
<br />

<br />
Group 1: War, Cle, Enc, Mnk, Dru,Nec
<br />
Group 2: War, Pal, Cle, Ber, Dru, Rng
<br />
Group 3: Rog, Rog, Wiz, Wiz, Mag, Brd
<br />
Group 4: SK, Shm, Cle, BL, Mnk, Enc.
<br />

<br />
Obivously each encounter would determine what your groups would be. The set up above is aiming at 3 balanced groups, with 1 dps group (as that would be a problem with only 24 peeps) supported by the bard. 
<br />

<br />
Anyone else thought of something like this, or do I have far too much time on my hands?! <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" /> </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
