				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Twenty Four<a name="71898"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jan 6 05 2:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Yup I had a Nec in group 1, but forgot to include it. Done that now. The Necro is there to twitch the Cleric.
<br />

<br />
Can see your argument for the zerker, but i was trying to include one of every class. If I took out the zerker, and one of the monks (going on the concept monk+bard = dream pull team) that leaves me:
<br />

<br />
Group 1: War, Cle, Enc, Mnk, Dru,Nec 
<br />
Group 2: War, Pal, Cle, Dru, Rng, (blank)
<br />
Group 3: Rog, Rog, Wiz, Wiz, Mag, Brd 
<br />
Group 4: SK, Shm, Cle, BL, Enc, (blank).
<br />

<br />
That leaves me 2 slots to fill. The idea of putting the Bard in group 3, was due to the lack of dps the raid is going to have. Every little helps when numbers are this tight, right?
<br />

<br />
So to fill the slots. I agree that group 3 is gonna need a healer, so lets swap the dru and mage over between 2 and 3. 
<br />

<br />
Group 1: War, Cle, Enc, Mnk, Dru,Nec 
<br />
Group 2: War, Pal, Cle, Mag, Rng, (blank)
<br />
Group 3: Rog, Rog, Wiz, Wiz, Dru, Brd 
<br />
Group 4: SK, Shm, Cle, BL, Enc, (blank).
<br />

<br />
Thats give us a healer in each group, and the druid can still nuke quite well when chance permits.
<br />

<br />
Now to fill the slots...... as mana is going to be an issue, how about a 2nd Necro in group 2 to feed the cleric? 
<br />
Just one more slot to fill now in group 4.  I think another Wiz will fill that well, to help burn the mobs down.
<br />

<br />
So here's another go:
<br />

<br />
Group 1: War, Cle, Enc, Mnk, Dru, Nec 
<br />
Group 2: War, Pal, Cle, Mag, Rng, Nec
<br />
Group 3: Rog, Rog, Wiz, Wiz, Dru, Brd 
<br />
Group 4: SK, Shm, Cle, BL, Enc, Wiz.
<br />

<br />
How far would this motely crew get then? And what problems (apart from lack of numbers of course) could be encountered?
<br />

<br />
