				<td colspan="2"><span>Ditch the SK and get another PAL, they are indispensible in higher level raids as offtankers.  Or maybe another SHM, a single SHM would be busy busy busy. 
<br />

<br />
Two Necs is probably unnecessary, I find the best use for nec's is the 'last man standing' syndrome.  You know the one, where your whole raid is dead and the nec is FD *phew*
<br />

<br />
I prefer DRU to WIZ, they don't have the DPS but they have much greater utility i.e. heals. Maybe replace one.
<br />

<br />
I raid with just such a small raid crew.  It was set up as a small efficient and fast raid crew.  The aim to be able to be at a target ready to go within a few minutes and to be able to hit and get out with greatest speed.  It works fabulously.  Small is beautiful and I have achieved more things with this small force than I have with one twice the size.   It is MUCH easier to manage.
<br />

<br />
However, you will be limited in the content you can address.  We ran into a brick wall with encounters like Rathe, Dust Avatar, Coirnav, RZtWL.  These encounters just require headcount, they are badly designed zergfests and with 24 people you will find these pretty much impossible. But don't underestimate the power of small raids.</span></td>
