				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, that's the wierd thing.  I'll be the first to admit, I've not met many zerkers, grouped with a couple in WoS now and then, and unfortunately, their tankage abilities was awful!  They both had real problems keeping aggro on them, causing a couple of group wipes.  Cleric was being pounded once for a while, yelling for help, and the poor zerker appeared to be unable todo anything about it. Zerker kept apologising profusely, and we all thought 'oh well, looks like they don't make good tanks, though maybe just that one'.  Wasn't too many days later had another zerker (thought we'd give it a go, just in case, and no tanks lfg).  Same result, we kept getting chewed up.  Now, 'tis true we are still unfamiliar with their role in a group, but it appears to be the same as a rogue, high melee dps, not too much mitigation/tank ability.  I'd of thought that they'd of been able to do more burst DPS than a rogue using disciplines tied to the endurance bar (wasn't this how it was advertised?).  As is, we've ended up waiting for a tank to be lfg rather than take the lfg zerker in the zone.  They need more mitigation, better aggro, though I guess that just turns them into Tank Clone whatever and doesn't give them much uniqueness that the other tanks have.  As for gear and AA's making them better, that applies to them all (best tank in WoS I met was a Darkwind Ranger hanging around in WoS waiting for a CoA raid, joined us for a bit and it was carnage).
<br />
Zerkers need some love it would appear, I'd love for them to be able to help groups as tanks more.
<br />

<br />
Jyve</span></td>
