&quot;Group 1: War, War, Cle, Brd, Mnk, Rog 
<br />
Group 2: Dru, Pal, Cle, Rog, Rng, Enc 
<br />
Group 3: Nec, Mag, Wiz, Wiz, Dru, Brd 
<br />
Group 4: Pal, Shm, Cle, BL, Enc, Nec &quot;
<br />

<br />
I haven't done much raiding but when moving from content to content I have really enjoyed the flexability of having a porter/evacer in every group. This in my limited experience helps move from target to target without the downtime. I know the raid leader tools now allow switching within the raid so perhaps this is not a realistic concern. 
<br />
One thing I would be concerned about is lack of a secondary or patch healer in the first group which is apparently going to contain both the MA and the Rampage Tanks. You can work a healing chain from outside the group but it does take more teamwork and communication.
<br />

<br />
How's this for a try?
<br />
Group 1: War, War, Cle, Brd, Mnk, Dru 
<br />
Group 2: Wiz, Pal, Cle, Rog, Rng, Enc 
<br />
Group 3: Nec, Mag, Rog, Wiz, Dru, Brd 
<br />
Group 4: Pal, Shm, Cle, BL, Enc, Nec 
<br />

